Note:
Java Emitter - Buffered output for Java code generation

All buffer management, character/string emission, and indentation logic
is delegated to the shared byte-buffer foundation in emitter_common.runa.
Java-specific punctuation helpers (emit_semicolon, emit_brace, ...) are
preserved on top of the shared primitives.

Conventions:
- 4-space indentation per Oracle Java code conventions
- Null-terminated output strings
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/emitter_common.runa" as EmitterCommon

@Reasoning:
Typed handle for the Java backend; the rich set of named punctuation
helpers keeps hir_to_java.runa free of magic byte literals.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Three fields shadow the raw EmitterCommon byte buffer.
@End Implementation

Type called "JavaEmitter":
    buffer as Integer
    capacity as Integer
    length as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
Factory entry hiding EmitterCommon from hir_to_java.runa.
@End Reasoning

Process called "create_java_emitter" returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_create from EmitterCommon
End Process

@Reasoning:
Lifecycle pair for create_java_emitter.
@End Reasoning

@Security_Scope:
Caller must guarantee the handle is live and not already destroyed.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "destroy_java_emitter" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_destroy from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process

@Reasoning:
Pre-sizing hook for large compilation units.
@End Reasoning

Process called "ensure_capacity" takes emitter as Integer, needed as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_ensure_capacity from EmitterCommon with emitter, needed
End Process

@Reasoning:
Single-byte primitive; named punctuation helpers below are preferred at
call sites for readability.
@End Reasoning

@Performance_Hints:
Hot path. O(1) amortized.
@End Performance_Hints

Process called "emit_char" takes emitter as Integer, char as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, char
End Process

@Reasoning:
Bulk emission for Java keywords (public, private, static, final, class,
interface, void, return) and identifiers.
@End Reasoning

@Performance_Hints:
Hot path. O(n) in input length.
@End Performance_Hints

Process called "emit_string" takes emitter as Integer, str as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, str
End Process

@Reasoning:
Convenience for a complete Java statement plus newline.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits the string then ASCII LF (10).
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_line" takes emitter as Integer, str as Integer returns Integer:
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, str
    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Standalone newline after block headers and between top-level declarations.
@End Reasoning

Process called "emit_newline" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
End Process

@Reasoning:
Spaces between Java tokens where required (around binary operators,
between modifier and type).
@End Reasoning

Process called "emit_space" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 32
End Process

@Reasoning:
Oracle Java code conventions specify 4-space indentation; matching this
gives clean diffs against IDE auto-format output.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Multiplies the indent level by 4 and emits that many ASCII SPACE bytes.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(level) bytes. Called once per emitted statement.
@End Performance_Hints

Process called "emit_indent" takes emitter as Integer, level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: 4-space indentation per Oracle Java code conventions.
    Let total_spaces be level multiplied by 4
    Let count be 0
    While count is less than total_spaces:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 32
        Set count to count plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Statement terminator; isolates the literal 59.
@End Reasoning

Process called "emit_semicolon" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 59
End Process

@Reasoning:
Argument/list separator; isolates the literal 44.
@End Reasoning

Process called "emit_comma" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 44
End Process

@Reasoning:
Member access operator; isolates the literal 46.
@End Reasoning

Process called "emit_dot" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 46
End Process

@Reasoning:
Label/case separator and ternary operator delimiter; isolates the
literal 58.
@End Reasoning

Process called "emit_colon" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 58
End Process

@Reasoning:
Block opener; isolates the literal 123.
@End Reasoning

Process called "emit_left_brace" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 123
End Process

@Reasoning:
Block closer; isolates the literal 125.
@End Reasoning

Process called "emit_right_brace" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 125
End Process

@Reasoning:
Expression grouping and argument-list opener; isolates the literal 40.
@End Reasoning

Process called "emit_left_paren" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 40
End Process

@Reasoning:
Expression grouping and argument-list closer; isolates the literal 41.
@End Reasoning

Process called "emit_right_paren" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 41
End Process

@Reasoning:
Array indexer and array-type bracket opener; isolates the literal 91.
@End Reasoning

Process called "emit_left_bracket" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 91
End Process

@Reasoning:
Array indexer and array-type bracket closer; isolates the literal 93.
@End Reasoning

Process called "emit_right_bracket" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 93
End Process

@Reasoning:
Annotation marker (@Override, @Deprecated); isolates the literal 64.
@End Reasoning

Process called "emit_at" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 64
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the accumulated Java source for the driver to hand to javac.
@End Reasoning

@Security_Scope:
Returned pointer aliases the emitter's internal buffer; do not free
directly and do not use after destroy_java_emitter.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "get_output" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process

@Reasoning:
Exposes current byte count for golden-output diff tools.
@End Reasoning

Process called "get_length" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_length from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process

@Reasoning:
Lets the driver reuse a single emitter across multiple compilation units.
@End Reasoning

Process called "reset" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_reset from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process
